                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced by the 3H(d,n)4He reaction",
                "using a continuous beam of 460 keV deuterons directed",
                "onto a tritiated titanium target, which consisted of a",
                "tritiated titanium layer, approximately 2.0 mg/cm2",
                "on a 0.5 mm silver backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Polypropylene foil with thickness of 3.8 mg/cm2",
                "mounted on a 0.5 mm thick tantalum backing located",
                "50.3 cm from the neutron-producing target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector system was made of 11",
                "fixed E-dE telescopes located at 0,+-12,+-24,+-36,",
                "+-48 and +-60deg with respect to the neutron beam axis",
                "in a scattering chamber. Detector thickness at each",
                "angle was optimized for given proton recoil energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
